image.altText: New Royal Adelaide Hospital building site Feb 19, 2015

props.synopsis: Almost eight years after it opened, a public hospital once branded Australia's most-expensive building continues to cost taxpayers, with more than $20 million spent last financial year alone on a long-running legal battle between its builder and the South Australian Government.

title.children: Royal Adelaide Hospital legal battle leaves taxpayers with $20 million bill

image.altText: A woman leans against an older man in a hat and striped shirt and an older woman wearing glasses, all smiling.

props.synopsis: Coroners will begin assessing if a learner driver who caused the death of three people was fit to drive. The 16-year-old was found guilty of careless driving, but not guilty of the more serious crime of causing death by dangerous driving.

title.children: Inquest to see if learner driver who caused triple fatal was fit to drive

image.altText: A paper sign taped to a black fence telling people about a childcare centre being shut down

props.synopsis: Genius Childcare at Blair Athol will be permanently shut down by its operators at the end of the month, despite being permitted to reopen by education regulators after addressing cleanliness concerns.

title.children: Adelaide childcare centre hit with cleanliness concerns to be shut down

image.altText: An overhead view of a mine site with large piles of soil and the outback landscape in the background.

props.synopsis: Miners were using a commonly-used chemical to stabilise ground in the Perilya Southern Operations mine when it ignited and caused a fire with potentially toxic fumes.

title.children: Regulator investigates how chemical sparked fire at Broken Hill mine

image.altText: One of two sheep that were found along an Adelaide road.

props.synopsis: Police swear they're not "trying to pull the wool over your eyes" with an appeal for public assistance to locate the owner of two sheep that were found at a major intersection in suburban Adelaide.

title.children: Sheep mystery as fleecy pair stop peak-hour traffic in Adelaide

image.altText: The police running sheet and poster relating to the missing Beaumont children.

props.synopsis: This weekend, another search for the remains of the Beaumont children will be undertaken at a former foundry site in Adelaide's west. For almost 60 years, the disappearance of nine-year-old Jane, seven-year-old Arnna and four-year-old Grant has baffled detectives.

title.children: The disappearance of the Beaumont children 'fundamentally changed society'

image.altText: A man with beard wearing white t-shirt with graphic in a backyard

props.synopsis: Rodney Clough has been sentenced to more than three years in jail for submerging his nephew's face in a sink filled with hot water. Taking into account time served, he is now eligible to apply for release on parole.

title.children: 'Frustration does not provide an excuse': Man who scalded 2yo with hot water sentenced

image.altText: An SA Police vehicle with flashing lights.

props.synopsis: A drink driver has allegedly returned an "unbelievable" alcohol reading of almost nine times the legal limit — a figure described by a South Australian police officer as so high that the driver should almost have been "in a coma".

title.children: Woman found asleep in car gives 'unbelievably high reading' in breath-test

image.altText: Lauren Willgoose walks alongside an older woman outside the court

props.synopsis: Lauren Jean Willgoose has asked a court to be sentenced to home detention for causing the crash which killed prominent neuropsychologist Anthony Walsh, because she would be "devastated" to be separated from her young son if she is jailed. Prosecutor Michael Foundas described her pregnancy as a "reckless decision".

title.children: Lawyer made 'reckless decision' to get pregnant while awaiting sentence

image.altText: An aerial shot of a vast outback landscape with a setting sun above it.

props.synopsis: The NSW environment minister says the purchase of Broughton Vale Station east of Broken Hill is a significant addition to the state's national parks portfolio.

title.children: Sacred Aboriginal birthing site part of 'significant' outback station sale

image.altText: A pink haired animated character points a spacey-gun at the camera, on another planet.

props.synopsis: This animated film created by an Adelaide couple is making waves internationally and is the only Australian feature selected for the coveted Berlin International Film Festival.

title.children: An animated film by these SA creators is taking Berlin by storm

image.altText: a man in a hat looks out over blackened trees

props.synopsis: One family who lost everything in the February 2024 Pomonal fire says they wouldn't be rebuilding if it wasn't for their love of the community.

title.children: Residents near Grampians vow to stay after two bushfires in 12 months

props.synopsis: Stunning new video has emerged of a Delta Air Lines flight crashing while attempting to land in Toronto, Canada, capturing the moment the passenger jet skids across the tarmac, catches fire, and rolls onto its roof.

title.children: Video shows moment Delta Air Lines flight crash-lands, catches fire and flips

props.synopsis: A police dog has escaped unscathed after the vehicle he was in was set alight in Adelaide’s north-eastern suburbs on Sunday.

title.children: Police dog escapes injury after patrol car set alight in Adelaide's north-east

image.altText: Dozens of dark-coloured, medium-sized whales lying on a beach.

props.synopsis: A group of more than 150 whales have stranded near Arthur River in Tasmania, with marine conservation experts responding.

title.children: Breaking: 'They're all struggling': More than 150 whales stranded in Tasmania's far north-west

image.altText: A man standing in front of a blue painting smiles gently

props.synopsis: What happened? Future historians might puzzle over this seismic shift in sentiment at the top of Australia's foremost public arts funding body.

title.children: Two videos show how quickly things can change in our fragmented world

image.altText: Police tape around a house damaged by fire.

props.synopsis: A woman and child have died and another two people are in a critical condition following a house fire in Sydney's west overnight.

title.children: Woman and child dead after 'horrific' house fire in Sydney's west

image.altText: Jim Chalmers holds his arms out while speaking at a press conference at parliament house

props.synopsis: Treasurer Jim Chalmers was quick to speak after the Reserve Bank cut rates. As welcome as the news might have been, he knew he couldn't be seen smiling.

title.children: It was the rate cut he wanted but Jim Chalmers knew not to smile

image.altText: Pope Francis grinning while wearing white robes and a silver Catholic cross chain and waving with his left hand

props.synopsis: A chest scan taken at Rome's Gemelli hospital shows the pontiff has developed bilateral pneumonia, after being treated earlier for asthmatic bronchitis and a complex respiratory infection.

title.children: Pope has pneumonia in both lungs, Vatican says

image.altText: A woman with brown hair walking on a footpath with her guide dog

props.synopsis: A Victorian woman is suing Uber in the Federal Court, alleging drivers breached disability discrimination laws by repeatedly refusing to pick up her guide dog.

title.children: 'I'm not a second-class citizen': Woman sues Uber over guide dog refusals

image.altText: A woman wearing a tan shirt holding a female child and an infant baby

props.synopsis: The wife and children of an Israeli hostage released a fortnight ago were killed during bombardment of Gaza.

title.children: Hamas to release remains of two young children and mother

image.altText: Group of men in a circle on Mudjimba beach

props.synopsis: Organisers say they are trying to promote wellness, peace, and connection within their communities through free activities. Then came the council bill.

title.children: Beach wellness gurus asked to pay up after anonymous complaints

image.altText: A group of men in suits sit at a huge wooden table in an ornate room with flowers, documents and water glasses on it

props.synopsis: The US Secretary of State met with Russian Foreign Minister Sergey Lavrov in Riyadh on Tuesday but Ukraine has said it will not accept a deal it is not party to.

title.children: Marco Rubio says Russia 'serious' about ending Ukraine war

image.altText: A construction worker on a house roof

props.synopsis: A new report says a national shortage of construction workers is impacting on Australia's housing supply, with the issue shaping up to be a key concern for voters this federal election.

title.children: Construction workforce issues leading to housing target shortfall

image.altText: Armed officers with helmets and bulletproof vests stand outside a large stadium in bright sunshine.

props.synopsis: For the first time since the 2009 terrorist attack on the Sri Lankan cricket team, Pakistan is once again showcasing its renowned hospitality by hosting the 2025 ICC Champions Trophy, welcoming international teams and fans.

title.children: After 16 years sidelined from hosting, Pakistan welcomes cricket tournament

image.altText: A man looks at a share price board outside the ASX in Sydney.

props.synopsis: A fall on Wall Street is likely to send Australian stocks lower, a day after the Reserve Bank cut interest rates for the first time in five years. Follow the latest updates in our live blog.

title.children: ASX to waver after interest rate cut, NAB, Santos profit results in focus

liveBlogKeyEvents.title: What to expect from today's Wage Price Index

image.altText: Gloved hands hold a petri dish with a sample of a meat-like substance in it.

props.synopsis: A Far North public health service says four people have died from melioidosis since New Year's Day and an investigation is underway to identify the cause of the increase in cases.

title.children: Soil-borne bacterial disease kills two more people in Queensland

image.altText: A hand is shown taking a test with pictures of Parliament House, the Australian Flag and a gavel in the background

props.synopsis: There's been a major decline in civics knowledge among school students, with many underperforming in their 2024 tests. Can you do any better?

title.children: Test your knowledge of civics to see if you can outperform a sixth grader

image.altText: A bright white circle, a black hole, surrounded by red accretion disc of hot gas and a flare.

props.synopsis: A black hole might conjure images of a dark, quiet void, but never-seen-before images captured by the James Webb Space Telescope reveals the centre of the Milky Way looks more like fireworks.

title.children: James Webb Space Telescope captures light show from Milky Way's black hole

image.altText: An aircraft identified by the Philippine Coast Guard as Chinese Navy helicopter flies close to a Philippines government  plane

props.synopsis: China has accused the Philippines of "spreading false narratives" after a second military incident with foreign aircraft over the South China Sea within a fortnight.

title.children: Chinese helicopter flies within 3m of Philippine plane in South China Sea

image.altText: A male and female couple in their late 40s smile at the camera in a selfie in front of a pool

props.synopsis: Craig and Lindsay Foreman were travelling through Iran on a world-wide trip when they were arrested.

title.children: British couple en route to Australia charged with espionage in Iran

image.altText: Haines in a white jacket speaks wearing glasses while Ryan listens next to her in a shiny teal jacket

props.synopsis: Crossbenchers including teal independents and the Greens say they will attempt to reform the federal corruption watchdog in the event of a hung parliament.

title.children: Crossbenchers push for NACC reforms after backflip on robodebt decision

image.altText: Alex de Minaur waves to the crowd with his left hand at the Rotterdam Open.

props.synopsis: Australian number one Alex de Minaur gets his first win as a 26-year-old, while Novak Djokovic goes down to Matteo Berrettini in his return from a hamstring injury at the Qatar Open.

title.children: Djokovic loses in return from injury, while de Minaur gets a win

image.altText: protesters in the Cook Islands

props.synopsis: Hundreds of protesters have taken to the streets in the Pacific nation of Cook Islands, urging the government to protect its ties with New Zealand.

title.children: Cook Islands PM facing no confidence vote over China pact

image.altText: Two women wearing blue and red Western Bulldogs AFLW kits smile at the camera with four people and city building behind them

props.synopsis: Sporting clubs like Chelsea have led the way on tailoring training to their players' menstrual cycles. But experts say the jury is still out on "phase based" interventions.

title.children: Menstrual cycle stigma continues to impact athletes, but one club is trying something new
